South Korean Census in year 2015 and 2020

Source: R/census_documentation.R, R/datasets.R
census.Rd

Census by sigungu.

Census by sigungu.

Usage

census

census

Format

A data frame with 253 rows and 11 variables:

adm1_code

Code of the province-level (Sido) administrative unit, as defined by KOSIS (Korean Statistical Information Service)

adm1_name

Name of the province-level (Sido) administrative unit, as defined by KOSIS

adm2_code

Code of the municipal-level (Sigungu) administrative unit, as defined by KOSIS; nested within adm1

adm2_name

Name of the municipal-level (Sigungu) administrative unit, as defined by KOSIS

pop2015_total

Total population according to the 2015 Census

pop2015_men

Male population according to the 2015 Census

pop2015_women

Female population according to the 2015 Census

pop2020_total

Total population according to the 2020 Census

pop2020_men

Male population according to the 2020 Census

pop2020_women

Female population according to the 2020 Census

A data frame with 253 rows and 11 variables:

adm1_code

Code of the province-level (Sido) administrative unit, as defined by KOSIS (Korean Statistical Information Service)

adm1_name

Name of the province-level (Sido) administrative unit, as defined by KOSIS

adm2_code

Code of the municipal-level (Sigungu) administrative unit, as defined by KOSIS; nested within adm1

adm2_name

Name of the municipal-level (Sigungu) administrative unit, as defined by KOSIS

adm2_plus

Sub-municipal districts (e.g., Bundang-gu, Ojeong-gu) within special-status cities (Teukrye-si) that have additional administrative autonomy

pop2015_total

Total population according to the 2015 Census

pop2015_men

Male population according to the 2015 Census

pop2015_women

Female population according to the 2015 Census

pop2020_total

Total population according to the 2020 Census

pop2020_men

Male population according to the 2020 Census

pop2020_women

Female population according to the 2020 Census
